                            <comment id="81338" author="niu" created="Thu, 10 Apr 2014 05:42:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you, Mahmoud.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="81311" author="mhanafi" created="Wed, 9 Apr 2014 17:22:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please close this case&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73906" author="niu" created="Fri, 20 Dec 2013 03:00:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This because lustre quota wasn&apos;t enabled however the ldiskfs quota on MDT was enabled, I&apos;m not sure how this happened, maybe such inconsisence was introduced by a partially executed quota on/off command.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;rerunning &lt;br/&gt;
lfs quotaoff -ug /nobackupp8&lt;br/&gt;
seems to have fixed the issue.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yes, a successful quota on/off can remove the inconsistence.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think the when the mds is reboot it enables quota. But lfs quota still reports that it is off.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If quota was enabled successfully, &apos;lfs quota&apos; shouldn&apos;t report off.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73877" author="pjones" created="Thu, 19 Dec 2013 19:21:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Niu&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please comment?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73876" author="mhanafi" created="Thu, 19 Dec 2013 19:10:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;rerunning &lt;br/&gt;
lfs quotaoff -ug /nobackupp8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;seems to have fixed the issue. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the when the mds is reboot it enables quota. But lfs quota still reports that it is off.&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
